The sequence \( \epsilon(n) = \omega_0 (-1)^n n^{-n} \) is the unique infinitesimal (up to choice of \( \omega_0 \)) that simultaneously satisfies information conservation, zero-mode normalizability, commutation with the $2I$-projectors, and negligible impact on the Seeley--DeWitt coefficients of the spectral action. Any deviation reintroduces information loss or breaks consistency with the right conoid geometry.
